# Complexity

## Time Complexity

```text
O(n)
```

Each node is visited and reversed at most once.

## Space Complexity

```text
O(1)
```

No extra data structures are used. Only pointers are used.

---

# Key Takeaways

```text
1. ptr checks whether a full k-group exists.
2. reverseLinkedList reverses exactly k nodes.
3. newHead stores the final answer head.
4. ktail connects the previous reversed group to the current reversed group.
5. The old head of a group becomes the tail after reversal.
6. Leftover nodes fewer than k are attached unchanged.
```

---

# Short Memory Trick

For every group:

```text
1. Check if k nodes exist.
2. Reverse k nodes.
3. Connect previous group tail to reversed head.
4. Update ktail to old head.
5. Move head to next group.
6. Attach leftovers at the end.
```
